<TITLE> Workers vandalise RMG factory in Narayanganj </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Narayanganj, Sept 18 (bdnews24.com)--Readymade garment workers on Friday vandalised an apparel factory, Knitting-Dyeing and Printing demanding back pay and bonuses at Rupganj Upazila in Narayanganj. The agitating workers also damaged four cars of the factory, police said. Eight workers including 'Makbul', 25, 'Shafiq', 25, 'Selim', 24, 'Ismail', 23, and 'Abu', 24, were also injured during the onslaught. The workers besieged Dhaka-Sylhet highway but lifted the blockade later as local MP Gazi Golam Dastagir assured them of making the factory authorities to clear up unpaid salaries and bonuses. Managing director of the factory, Akbar Ali, said the workers were supposed to be paid on Saturday. Officer in charge of Rupganj Police Station, Forkan Sikder, said the situation was now under control. The authorities will clear salaries and bonuses on Saturday, he added. 
